09/03/2008
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Retired Croatian General Ante Gotovina and two other generals will face The Hague war crimes tribunal on Tuesday (March 11th), Presiding Judge Alphonse Orie announced at a status conference Friday (March 7th). 
Gotovina, Ivan Cermak and Mladen Markac are charged with war crimes and crimes against humanity committed during the 1995 Operation Storm. 
Between 150,000 and 200,000 ethnic Serbs fled during the operation, and more than 150 Serb civilians were killed. 
(AFP, Vecernji List, HINA, Javno.com - 07/03/08)
